  "text": "Prometheus remote write endpoints enforce TLS and authentication through multiple mechanisms:\n\n**TLS Configuration Validation:**\nIn config/config.go (lines 1448-1477), RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML validates TLS settings by calling HTTPClientConfig.Validate() at line 1473. This validates the TLS configuration from the prometheus/common/config package, which includes certificate verification, CA certificates, and client certificates.\n\n**Authentication Configuration Validation:**\nThe validateAuthConfigs function in config/config.go (lines 1491-1515) enforces that at most one authentication method is configured for remote write endpoints, checking for: basic_auth (BasicAuth), authorization (Bearer tokens via custom Authorization type), oauth2, sigv4, azuread, and google_iam. This validation is called from RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML at line 1477.\n\n**Bearer Token Handling:**\nIn storage/remote/azuread/azuread.go, the AzureADConfig.Validate() method (lines 131-223) validates Azure AD configuration parameters. The NewAzureADRoundTripper function (lines 237-256) creates an HTTP round tripper that injects Bearer tokens. The azureADRoundTripper.RoundTrip method (lines 260-268) sets the Authorization header with a Bearer token (line 265-266): 'bearerAccessToken := \"Bearer \" + accessToken'.\n\n**Basic Auth and Other Auth Methods:**\nThe validateHeaders function in config/config.go (lines 1529-1538) prevents manual authorization header injection, requiring users to use designated auth parameters instead. This ensures proper handling of basic_auth, authorization headers, and other authentication mechanisms.\n\n**Client Setup with Auth and TLS:**\nThe storage/remote/client.go file contains ClientConfig struct (lines 128-141) and NewWriteClient function (lines 183-238). NewWriteClient creates an HTTP client via config_util.NewClientFromConfig (line 188) which applies TLS configuration from HTTPClientConfig, then wraps the transport with authentication round trippers for SigV4 (lines 198-202), Azure AD (lines 205-209), and Google IAM (lines 212-216).\n\n**Remote Read Endpoints:**\nRemoteReadConfig.UnmarshalYAML (lines 1613-1628) similarly validates TLS and headers for remote read endpoints using the same validateHeaders function and HTTPClientConfig.Validate() call.\n\n**Google Cloud IAM:**\nThe storage/remote/googleiam/googleiam.go NewRoundTripper function (lines 34-54) creates a Google Cloud authenticated HTTP transport using either credentials files or default credentials, implementing the monitoring.write scope."
}

